Class JibeEvent

public class JibeEvent
extends java.lang.Object

Base class for all Jibe Service events. This class also contains a collection of event-related, static helper methods.

TYPE_UNKNOWN

public static final int TYPE_UNKNOWN
Unknown event. An occurance of this event indicates that an error has occurred.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

INFO_GENERIC_EVENT

public static final int INFO_GENERIC_EVENT
Info value, indicating that the event is generic. Either no additional info is necessary, or two events of the same type have merged into one during throttling. For example, if a contact's telephone number and address were both changed, only one generic 'contact changed' event would be sent.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

SOURCE_GENERIC_EVENT

public static final int SOURCE_GENERIC_EVENT
Source value, indicating that the event is generic. Either no specific source is available or two events of the same type have been merged into one during throttling. For example, if a contact's telephone number and address were both changed, only one generic 'contact changed' event would be sent.

makeGeneric

public void makeGeneric()
Removes the additional info and source from this event, and turns it into a generic one. This method is invoked if two events are merged into one for throttling. For example, if a contact's telephone number and address were both changed, only one generic 'contact changed' event would be sent.

isGeneric

public boolean isGeneric()
Indicates whether the event is generic, i.e. it has no specific source, nor any additional info. This can happen if two events are merged into one, for throttling. For example, if a contact's telephone number and address were both changed, only one generic 'contact changed' event would be sent.

Returns:
true if the event is generic.
